CTRL-L clears the screen like clear does
%
fc opens the last run command in $EDITOR and runs it again after it was edited
%
CTRL-x, CTRL-e opens an $EDITOR containing whatever is currently entered in the prompt
%
lsof - shows open file handles, sockets, etc.
%
to run the last command with sudo prepended run sudo !!
%
^start^stop is used to replace parts of a previous commands and run it again
